# Test: two-tier dispatch delivers all routes under load with overflow
# VALIDATES: AC-10/AC-11/AC-12 -- burst exceeding channel capacity triggers
#   overflow dispatch, all routes delivered without loss and in order
# PREVENTS: routes dropped during overflow, two-tier dispatch path untested
#   end-to-end through real reactor
#
# Flow:
# 1. ze.fwd.chan.size=2 forces a tiny per-worker channel (overflow guaranteed)
# 2. Source peer sends 80 UPDATEs in a burst
# 3. Destination peer asserts all 80 NLRIs arrive in order, then EOR
# 4. Python observer smoke-checks metric registration while the tiny channel
#    and full destination delivery prove the overflow path was taken

